There are different services provided by kubernetes 
Service Types:
==============
1) ClusterIP 
When you create service by choosing type ClusterIP, what exactly it mans.You can access this service with in this cluster .
It get one private IP and this is accessible only within the cluster.
You can not access service type CLusterIP from the out side world.

To create service yaml in dry run method

# kubectl expose deployment pyapp --name=pyapp-service --port=80 --target-port=8000 --protocol=TCP --type=ClusterIP --dry-run=client -o yaml > pyapp-svc.yaml
# kubectl appl -f pyapp-svc.yaml

when should we use ClusterIP:
=============================
Suppose we deploying database inside the cluster . Obviousely this database must be accessible only within the cluster. No one from outside can access database directly .
for this we want a sable endpoint, So create a service of type clusterIP so that application running inside the cluster will access this database. No one from outside 
the cluster can directly access database.
